12/10/2003
WASHINGTON, United States -- The US State Department praised the decision by Turkey and Greece to call off their regular military exercises on the island of Cyprus on Friday (10 October).
"We think the decision contributes to building a positive atmosphere for reaching a comprehensive Cyprus settlement and stability in the Aegean region," State Department Spokesman Richard Boucher said.
Turkey and Greece have also said they will call off naval exercises in the eastern Mediterranean scheduled for autumn.
(AP, AFP - 10/10/03)
